V<p><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chris_Hadfield">Chris Hadfield</a> (August 1959-) is a Canadian astronaut currently on assignment aboard the International Space Station. He will become the first Canadian Commander of the ISS when Expedition 35 takes over this March.</p>\u000a<p>Hadfield has become an Internet-celebrity, using social media and YouTube to share what daily life is like aboard the ISS. He regularly <a href="https://twitter.com/Cmdr_Hadfield">tweets</a> breath-taking photos of Earth (<a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2013/02/26/chris-hadfield-photos-from-space_n_2768497.html#slide=2157665">here is a selection of his best pics</a>) and has a <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/canadianspaceagency">YouTube channel</a> with videos on everything from how he operates a giant robotic arm to how he eats a peanut butter and honey pita sandwich (bread isn&#8217;t used because of the crumbs). This particular quote is taken from a recent <a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/alexkantrowitz/2013/02/18/five-highlights-from-commander-chris-hadfields-reddit-ama-from-space/">Redditt &#8216;Ask me anything&#8217;</a> session Hadfield took part in while aboard the ISS. A youngster asked if Hadfield had any advice for an aspiring astronaut, and this quote was his reply.</p>\u000a<p class="notes">- Thanks to Jason for submitting this.<br />\u000a- RELATED COMICS: <a href="http://zenpencils.com/comic/76-neil-armstrong-a-giant-among-men/">Neil Armstrong.</a> <a href="http://zenpencils.com/comic/33-edgar-mitchell-a-global-consciousness/">Edgar Mitchell.</a> <a href="http://zenpencils.com/comic/100-carl-sagan-pale-blue-dot/">Carl Sagan.</a> <a href="http://zenpencils.com/comic/64-robert-h-goddard-the-rocket-man/">Robert Goddard.</a> <a href="http://zenpencils.com/comic/52-phil-plait-welcome-to-science/">Phil Plait.</a> <a href="http://zenpencils.com/comic/42-neil-degrasse-tyson-the-most-astounding-fact/">Neil deGrasse Tyson.</a></p>\u000a<p class="print"><a href="