V<p><img alt="spanishpic" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1594" height="162" src="http://maxcdn.zenpencils.com/wp-content/uploads/spanishpic.jpg?9d7bd4" width="580" /></p>\u000a<p><strong>Check out the new <a href="http://zenpencils.com/translations/">TRANSLATIONS</a> page.</strong></p>\u000a<p>Over the past year, readers have translated some of my comics \u2013 sometimes for a school project, for their own blog or so they can just share it with their friends privately. I&#8217;ve finally started organising them and have put together a <a href="http://zenpencils.com/translations/">translations</a> page. As you can see, there are only a handful so far and I would love to have more and in as many languages as possible. That&#8217;s where you come in &#8211; I obviously can&#8217;t translate them myself because I&#8217;m only (barely) fluent in English, so I need you, my lovely readers, to translate the comics for me. I can provide lo-res comics with the English words removed so it&#8217;s easy for you to just place the translated words on top. You can do whichever one you like and as many or as few as you like. With your help, we could turn this into a truly international website!</p>\u000a<p>So send me an <a href="mailto:gavin@zenpencils.com">email</a> if you&#8217;re interested <img alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" src="http://maxcdn.zenpencils.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif?9d7bd4" /> </p>\u000a<p><em>To my many Brazilian fans: I&#8217;ve already got some people working on Portuguese/Brazilian translations, they should be available soon.</em></p>
